notes.title: Vorstellungsgespr√§ch Naheed
notes.content:
- Briefly introduce myself and explain that I am the IT manager
- Ask how they would like to be addressed
- Ask them to briefly introduce themselves


Among other things, I am responsible for our internal infrastructure, IT security, data protection issues, and supporting our end devices (laptops for employees). We provide IT for our employees and also develop some solutions for specialist departments and projects. Among other things, we have started to develop applications (expert database, calculation aid for travel times, insurance management software, etc.) and develop tailor-made AI solutions for projects and project work.

There are currently two of us in our IT department. Besides me, there is Ashik, who provides first-level support and develops applications.
 
IT security is a well-known topic for you. Banking sector and genomics


We work in accordance with BSI standards and ISO 27001.

If you are hired, you will work with us in various areas. Part of your working time will be spent in internal IT.
- Linux server support and Linux desktops
- Coordination of security risks, emergency planning, and GDPR implementation.

I am particularly interested in how you work in these areas and where you see yourself ‚Äì both technically and in terms of collaboration with other teams.

- Which Linux distribution do you prefer for servers? In CV: redhat and Debian. Why?
- How do you deal with distribution updates and upgrades? What do you do if security vulnerabilities are known but an update/upgrade is not currently possible?
- Do you have experience with server virtualization via Proxmox?

- Have you had any contact with data protection requirements in previous projects? Can you give an example?
- How do you handle the storage and processing of personal data?
- What measures would you take to ensure that data transfers are GDPR-compliant?
- Are you familiar with the most important principles of the GDPR? (Lawfulness, processing in good faith, transparency, purpose limitation, data minimization, integrity and confidentiality, accountability

- How do you assess the risk of a new application or architecture?
- Do you have experience in creating emergency or recovery plans?
- Are you familiar with the most important elements of a security concept?
- How do you document security measures so that they remain traceable for others?
- Do you have experience with backup strategies for large amounts of data (> TB range)?
- Have you ever been involved in ISO 27001 certification?
- How do you document technical and organizational measures (TOM)?
- Describe a project that went wrong. What did you learn from it?

- Are there any topics that would be particularly important to you if you started here?
- Do you have any questions?
